      h3.title Uncoupled Networks
      p.projwords The oughtomation method implements “rules-as-data” with simple input/output control-tables that work with any programming language, when accompanied with a suitable parsing library. Loose coupling of components and data means interchangeable alternative implementations, to avoid misplaced restrictions relating to platform, programming language, operating system or supplier, which  clash with edge-based prerogative. This avoids “rules as code” lock-in where algorithms are expressed in various incompatible procedural programming languages.
